Package proxy

Class ClientProxy

java.lang.Object
proxy.ClientProxy
public class ClientProxy extends Object
The client communicates through the ClientProxy class. This class is where the proxy connection point starts. Upon connection, the ClientProxy will attempt to connect to the end node; then the intermediary node; then the guard node. After that, messages and requests can be relayed

    • createProxy

      public Proxy createProxy(String proxyAddress, int proxyPort)
      Using this constructor will create a SOCKS proxy that is able to: - Connect to the nodes using TLS (create circuits) and key exchange - Communicate with servers through the nodes using AES encryption - Send/receive cells using the built-in SOCKS library The proxy instance will be created through the Java PROXY APIs SOCKS-type The connection is created through the use of the openConnection(proxy) method
      Parameters:
      proxyPort - is the port that the will run on
      proxyAddress - is the address URL where the proxy will reside

    • retrievePayload

      public void retrievePayload(RelayCell cell)
      When reading a stream of cells, each cell is decrypted. After that, this method is called for each of the cell. When the final cell is received, the total message is sent to the browser.
      Parameters:
      cell - is the cell received from the onion router at the end (endNode).

    • sendCell

      public void sendCell(ArrayList<Node> routers, int hops, Cell cell)
      Method created for high code-composition. Method takes care of encryption depending on how many hops the specified cell needs
      Parameters:
      routers - are all the nodes in the current circuit
      hops - are how many nodes ahead this cell should be sent (aka. the number of times we encrypt)
      cell - the cell we wish to send could be both relay -and command cell)

    • receiveCell

      public byte receiveCell(Cell cell, ArrayList<Node> routers) throws Exception
      Support-method created to make handling of received cells easier Method interprets the type of cell (command), and returns it Method can be used in general receie-method in order to use the correct method for handling the cell (ex: created() or relayExtended())
      Parameters:
      cell - is the cell that was received
      routers - are all the routers in the circuit
      Returns:
      the command present in the cell after decryption (must be numbers 0-3)
      Throws:
      Exception
